        • mResultDelay

          int mResultDelay
          This represents how late the results are. When we spawn a task to calculate the path, we reset this to 0. If the results come back by the beginning of the next frame, then no frames have been skipped and we can use the input list as-is. But if the results don't come back, then the results are based on old data and we must keep track of the missed frames so we can skip them in the input queue.
